The paper proposes a novel architecture for learning multiple driving behaviors in a traffic scenario using reinforcement learning and multi-agent learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of parameter sharing and asynchronous updates, which are common techniques in deep learning and machine learning, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on multi-agent learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed framework to robotics, indicating that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper discusses the cooperation between agents, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
